description: Securing a daily meal is never a guarantee in war-torn Gaza. Many Gazans report that they are receiving little to no aid from abroad, despite the outpouring of donations from the international community. NBC News documents two displaced families and their everyday struggle of trying to secure one meal in Rafah.
title: The daily struggle for food in Gaza: Battling hunger in a war zone

description: An artificial intelligence candidate is on the ballot for the United Kingdom’s general election next month.
title: AI candidate running for Parliament in the U.K. says AI can humanize politics

description: TEL AVIV — Israeli troops stationed on the Lebanese border fired a medieval-style siege weapon known as a trebuchet amid recent fighting against Hezbollah militants, an Israeli military official confirmed to NBC News.
title: Israeli troops use medieval-style trebuchet weapon in fighting at Lebanon border

description: A special judge’s court in Bangladesh on Wednesday indicted Nobel laureate Muhammad Yunus and 13 others on charges in an over $2 million embezzlement case.
title: Bangladesh court indicts Nobel laureate Muhammad Yunus on charges of embezzlement

description: Around 1,000 BTS fans were given the chance to get a hug from Jin as part of the annual FESTA event in Seoul, South Korea. It was Jin's first public event since he ended 18 months of national service in the army.
title: BTS fans line up to hug Jin after his discharge from the South Korean army

description: Argentina’s Senate began what’s likely to be an all-night voting marathon on the details of President Javier Milei ‘s sweeping proposals to slash spending and boost his own powers early Thursday, shortly after giving the plan overall approval in a narrow vote as thousands of protesters clashed with police outside.
title: Protesters clash with police as Milei’s radical overhaul advances in Argentina’s Senate

description: Argentine protesters set fires and clashed with police in the streets outside Congress on Wednesday, as lawmakers kicked off debate of a sprawling bill that is key to new libertarian President Javier Milei's economic reform plans.
title: Argentine riot police fire water cannons and tear gas to disperse protesters outside Congress

description: A Florida court has found the banana brand Chiquita liable for funding a paramilitary group during the Colombian civil war. The company has been ordered to pay a total of $38.3 million to more than a dozen relatives of the victims of the military group.
title: Chiquita found liable for funding paramilitary group during Colombia civil war
